    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>The barrow-wight is a barrow-warden who has undergone a second, terrible transformation — its connection to the Rot deepening until ancient barrow-magic fuses with corruption, creating something more powerful and far more willful than the common draugr. Barrow-wights retain the commanding presence of their former role but now exert it through fear and corruption rather than martial authority. Their very gaze can wither resolve, and they draw strength from the despair of their enemies.</p>",
